The paper presents a distributed algorithm for computing the mixing time of undirected graphs, which involves analyzing connectivity and expansion properties of the network. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Data Structures and Algorithms, Social and Information Networks, Network Science and Graph Theory sub-categories. Among these, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on designing an efficient distributed algorithm for computing the mixing time. The other categories are also relevant, as they involve analyzing network properties and could be related to the paper's approach.
